throne /θrəʊn/

(thrones) 

1. N-COUNT A throne is a decorative chair used by a king, queen, or emperor on important official occasions. (君王的) 宝座 

2. N-SING You can talk about the throne as a way of referring to the position of being king, queen, or emperor. 王位; 皇位 

例： ...the queen's 40th anniversary on the throne. ...女王登位40周年纪念日。

